{
  "updated_prompt": "Given `question` and `summary_1`, produce a single compact second-hop BM25 search query (only the query string; no explanation).\n\nKeep all existing reversibility constraints and optimization rules from the prior prompt (preserve anchors and uncertainty; do not invent new entities or facts; do not output multiple queries). In addition, when the first-hop retrieval returned season/event pages or franchise overview pages but failed to surface the missing person biography page, bias the second-hop query toward answer-bearing player/biography pages by explicitly adding short relation/role terms that signal player lists or bios. Concretely, when the goal is to verify a player who both (a) appeared on a specific team in a specific season and (b) attended a named college, include the team+season anchor and the college anchor together with one compact role/relation term such as roster, roster list, player, biography, or \"played college\". For example use the pattern: <team-season> <college> <roster|player|biography|played college> (adaptively choose one or two short terms). Avoid adding broad event/location words that retrieve season summaries only. Preserve any uncertain candidate names from the inputs (do not assert them). The final query must be a concise keyword query suitable for BM25 retrieval (no boolean/meta operators, no site:), and should prefer terms that identify player/biography pages over generic season pages.",
  "rationale": "The failure was retrieving season/event pages instead of a player biography page. Instructing the writer to append compact relation/role terms (e.g., roster, player, biography, played college) to the existing team-season + college anchors steers BM25 toward person/roster pages that are more likely to contain the answer, while preserving reversibility and not inventing new entities."
}
